            <title>[CASSANDRA-15409] nodetool compactionstats showing extra pending task for TWCS</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-15409</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Summary: nodetool compactionstats showing extra pending task for TWCS&lt;br/&gt;
-----------------&lt;br/&gt;
The output of &lt;tt&gt;nodetool compactionstats}}can show &quot;pending tasks: 1&quot; when there are actually none. This seems to be a consistent problem in testing C* trunk. In my testing, it looks like the {{nodetool compactionstats&lt;/tt&gt; counter output is consistently off by 1 as compared to the table output of the tasks&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;testing with &lt;tt&gt;concurrent_compactors: 8&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In 12 hours it never ended, always showing 1 pending job&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
